      "problems": "Multiple failures occurred during the Docker image build process, primarily related to the installation of Miniconda and Miniforge. The specific error messages included: 'failed ELF opening leading to a non-zero exit code' during Miniconda installation, and 'unknown query {CWE}' when running the tests. The Docker build often failed at steps involving the installation of these dependencies, indicating potential compatibility or configuration issues. Additionally, there were issues with missing files, specifically 'src/iris.py', which caused subsequent attempts to run the script to fail.",
      "actions": "1. Initiated the Docker build with a Dockerfile based on Ubuntu 22.04 and added commands to install dependencies. 2. Attempted to install Miniconda but faced ELF file errors and build failures. 3. Switched to Miniforge as an alternative, which also resulted in installation failures. 4. Modified the Dockerfile to include commands to accept terms of service for Conda channels before installation. 5. Successfully set up the Conda environment with the provided 'environment.yml', but subsequent queries against the script failed due to missing parameters and files. 6. Attempted to run tests which failed due to unknown queries.",
      "progress": "50% complete. The Conda environment was created successfully, and the Docker image was built after several iterations. However, the project is still not fully functional due to missing files and parameters required for testing. The Docker container is operational but does not currently execute tests successfully.",
      "lessons": "The project requires specific versions of Miniconda or Miniforge for compatibility. The installation of dependencies needs careful handling of environment variables and terms of service acceptance. The script 'src/iris.py' requires specific input parameters which were not provided. Compatibility issues with ELF files suggest a need to verify the architecture compatibility of the dependencies being installed.",
      "suggestions": "1. Verify the architecture compatibility of the Miniconda or Miniforge installer being used. 2. Ensure the 'src/iris.py' script exists and is accessible before executing it. 3. When running tests, provide valid query parameters instead of placeholders like '{CWE}'. 4. Consider using a stable version of Miniforge known to work with Ubuntu 22.04. 5. Review the README.md for any specific requirements or configurations not yet addressed. 6. If the current approach continues to fail, consider using a pre-built Docker image known to work for this project.",
      "dockerfile_recommendation": "FROM ubuntu:22.04\n\nARG DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive\nENV TZ=Europe/Berlin\n\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y git curl wget\nRUN apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends tzdata bash ca-certificates python3 python3-pip\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\nRUN git clone https://github.com/iris-sast/iris.git\nWORKDIR /app/iris\n\nENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda\nENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH\n\nRUN wget --quiet https://github.com/conda-forge/miniforge/releases/download/4.10.3-10/Miniforge3-Linux-x86_64.sh -O /tmp/miniforge.sh && \\\n    chmod +x /tmp/miniforge.sh && \\\n    /tmp/miniforge.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR && \\\n    rm /tmp/miniforge.sh && \\\n    conda clean -afy\n\nRUN conda tos accept --override-channels --channel https://repo.anaconda.com/pkgs/main \\\n    && conda tos accept --override-channels --channel https://repo.anaconda.com/pkgs/r\n\nCOPY environment.yml /app/iris/\nRUN conda env create -f environment.yml\n\nSHELL [\"/bin/bash\", \"-c\"]\nRUN echo \"conda activate iris\" >> ~/.bashrc\n\nCMD [\"/bin/bash\"]",
      "dockerfile_used": "FROM ubuntu:22.04\n\nARG DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive\nENV TZ=Europe/Berlin\n\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y git\n\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \\\n    tzdata bash ca-certificates \\\n    curl sudo nano software-properties-common vim wget python3 python3-pip unzip tar apt-transport-https lsb-release \\\n    && ln -snf /usr/share/zoneinfo/$TZ /etc/localtime \\\n    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\nRUN git clone https://github.com/iris-sast/iris.git\n\nWORKDIR /app/iris\n\nENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda\nENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH\n\nRUN wget --quiet https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-latest-Linux-aarch64.sh -O /tmp/miniconda.sh && \\\n    chmod +x /tmp/miniconda.sh && \\\n    /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR && \\\n    rm /tmp/miniconda.sh && \\\n    conda clean -afy\n\nRUN conda tos accept --override-channels --channel https://repo.anaconda.com/pkgs/main \\\n    && conda tos accept --override-channels --channel https://repo.anaconda.com/pkgs/r\n\nRUN conda env create -f environment.yml\n\nSHELL [\"/bin/bash\", \"-c\"]\nRUN echo \"conda activate iris\" >> ~/.bashrc\n\nCMD [\"/bin/bash\"]"
